2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,279
{\an8}AN ADAPTATION OF THE NOVEL BY HUDANAJWA

3
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:10,279
{\an8}I told you, darling.

4
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,200
Just do whatever you want.

5
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:15,680
{\an8}Plus, I believe in you

6
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:18,760
{\an8}and I love you so much.

7
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:21,520
{\an8}You are a woman.

8
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,840
{\an8}Women are special.

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:29,280
{\an8}A woman has no limit
to her love for someone.

10
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:32,320
I'm not upset.

11
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:35,400
{\an8}I'm thankful. Thankful for you.

12
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:41,040
Dear.

13
00:00:41,720 --> 00:00:42,560
Yes.

14
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:46,400
I'm pregnant.

15
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,160
My goodness.

16
00:00:56,840 --> 00:01:00,039
Darling, do you know that you are
the most special person in my life?

17
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:02,879
When I married you,
it was like a dream come true.

18
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:05,999
I don't really think about children,
but when Auntie's family

19
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,120
and yours said that you were barren,
I felt upset.

20
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:12,400
I pray every single day.

21
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:17,800
I pray to God
that He will let you get pregnant.

22
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,480
No one in this world
can humiliate you, darling.

23
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:26,240
Thank God. You are pregnant, darling.

24
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:37,400
Yes! I'm going to be a father!

25
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,679
I...

26
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:45,200
I can't wait to see the baby's face.
I'm sure it'll be cute like you.

27
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:48,559
But when I found out back then,

28
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:51,759
I really wanted this baby
to look like you.

29
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,280
Tall, handsome, fair.

30
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:57,280
Back then?

31
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:03,880
Are you serious right now?

32
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,160
You knew you were pregnant
and you didn't tell me?

33
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,159
I...

34
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,800
- I forgot.
- Forgot?

35
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:18,079
{\an8}Am I not important in your life?
You forgot to tell me something like this?

36
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,559
{\an8}No. No, dear.

37
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:21,680
{\an8}Now I know. I understand it now.

38
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:27,720
Dear.

39
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,800
Dear. Please open the door.

40
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,280
Please open the door.

41
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,080
Honey, please.

42
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:03,440
Hey, dear.

43
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:08,159
- Why did you follow me?
- Hey!

44
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:10,400
- I'm not important, right?
- Dear, no.

45
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,919
Dear, okay, fine.

46
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:20,159
I didn't tell you that time
because I was angry with you, dear.

47
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,520
That's it.

48
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,879
I know, dear.
I shouldn't have kept this from you.

49
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:32,440
I know it's my fault
and I'm sorry. Okay? Please.

50
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,680
It's my fault.

51
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:41,520
I was too busy working
to know you were pregnant.

52
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,800
I'm sorry.

53
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:50,840
I should be taking care of you
at this early stage, but I wasn't around.

54
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,240
What if something happened
to you or the baby?

55
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,880
I would regret it.

56
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,199
My baby.

57
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,799
Let me tell you this.

58
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:16,800
Your father is the strongest man
in the world.

59
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:23,680
I don't want you to be scared
of anyone or anything, okay?

60
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:28,800
Papa will take care of us.

61
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,360
Please promise me, darling.

62
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:49,120
We will take care of our baby together.

63
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,480
God willing, darling.

64
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,640
I love you, Thariq Ridzuwan.

65
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,560
I love you too, my treasure.

66
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,640
Congratulations to Adrean,

67
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,639
Thariq, and all the members

68
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:33,759
of the Holy Dragon, for successfully
suppressing the Gajah Hitam syndicate.

69
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,360
Thank you, sir.

70
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,920
How about Farez?

71
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,479
His last location was in Yangon, Myanmar.

72
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,079
We will watch him closely.

73
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:45,080
If he crosses the border, we will know.

74
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:47,720
Permission, sir.

75
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,679
My wife is pregnant.

76
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,879
Thank God. Congratulations, Thariq.

77
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:54,920
Thank you, sir.

78
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:59,439
I'd like permission to work in the camp
throughout her pregnancy

79
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,800
and until delivery, sir.

80
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:03,920
Won't you miss working in the field?

81
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:05,720
I will,

82
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,400
but if I'm far away from her,
I'll miss her more.

83
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:13,960
Very well.

84
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:17,120
I approve your application.

85
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,400
Thank you, sir.

86
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,840
All the menus here are delicious.

87
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,519
Is it your first time?

88
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,639
No, I've been here two years.

89
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:38,119
I eat here every day.

90
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:40,920
Two years? Every day?

91
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:45,719
So 365 times 2 equals 730.

92
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:49,240
That's 730 days straight.

93
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,399
Seriously, bro?

94
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:54,720
So what? I want to think before ordering.

95
00:06:55,920 --> 00:07:00,279
Sure, but don't do it
when you're already in front.

96
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:01,759
She's right.

97
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:04,079
We've been waiting for 15 minutes.

98
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:07,119
Please be considerate.
Others want to eat as well.

99
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,279
Miss.

100
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:11,039
Think first, then get in the line.

101
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:14,239
You're so well-built,
but you have a small brain.

102
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,759
What would you like?

103
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:20,359
One spicy set, one original set.
Add on cheesy wedges and one sundae cone.

104
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:23,079
- Okay.
- Give everything she ordered to me.

105
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,199
Make two sets, please.

106
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,680
One for him and one for me.
I'll pay for him. Win.

107
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:34,640
He pushed me.

108
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,479
Bro, sorry.

109
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:40,759
My wife is pregnant. So her mood is like--

110
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,239
Don't think I'm stupid.

111
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,079
She's short like a schoolkid.

112
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:46,879
And she's pregnant?
Isn't she too short for that?

113
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,839
Hey, she's my wife.

114
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:50,519
Ever heard of a hormonal imbalance?

115
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,240
This isn't an imbalance. This is crazy.

116
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,999
- Thariq...
- Stay quiet.

117
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,119
Now you apologize.

118
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:05,079
He pushed me, calling me crazy and short.

119
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,279
Now I have to apologize?

120
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,720
My principle is that

121
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,839
if we made a mistake,
it's still our fault.

122
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,919
Just apologize. It's as easy as that.

123
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,960
No.

124
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:21,159
Darling, please apologize,
so I have a reason to talk to him.

125
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,839
He's all brawn and no brain.
I can beat him up.

126
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:26,080
Go apologize. Now.

127
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,120
Bro.

128
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:36,639
Sorry, I shouldn't have cut your line.
I'm really sorry.

129
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:38,839
You're not only short,
but you're also rude.

130
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,080
What did you say?

131
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:43,479
Don't call my wife short.

132
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:45,240
Don't call my wife crazy.

133
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,200
Most importantly, don't touch her.
Hear me?

134
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:50,560
- Did you?
- Yes.

135
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:57,799
Okay, it's ready.

136
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,679
Please count for everyone.

137
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,159
I'm paying. How much?

138
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,000
I'll use my QR. Is 1,000 enough?

139
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,240
I paid 1,000. Thank you.

140
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,120
Let's go.

141
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:29,680
Yes, darling.

142
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,440
I want to say thank you.

143
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:33,920
Why?

144
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:39,039
For defending me at the restaurant,
even though it was my fault.

145
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:41,279
It's my job to protect you.

146
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,920
Whatever the reason is.

147
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,920
What should I do
if you're not around, dear?

148
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,520
If you don't want me gone,

149
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,519
don't go anywhere.

150
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,720
I won't go anywhere.

151
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,359
But if I die...

152
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:06,080
My God. What are you saying, darling?

153
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:09,839
I pray for you and our baby
to be healthy every day.

154
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:12,279
Please don't say that.
What were you thinking?

155
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:16,679
A prayer is an effort,
but we can't change God's fate.

156
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:19,640
We hold on to this saying,

157
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:24,199
"Whoever strives, achieves."

158
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:27,439
But we still have to believe this too.
"Be, and it becomes."

159
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:31,200
God responds to the way
His servant perceives Him.

160
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:38,999
If His servant thinks positively,
positive things will follow.

161
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,239
I love our child.

162
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:44,840
I've never
and will never think negatively of God.

163
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:46,760
So,

164
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,400
don't stop praying.

165
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,280
Okay?

166
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:11,319
Dear God, please. Please.

167
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:14,799
Dear, come here.

168
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,079
Still have something to say?

169
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,679
- Yes.
- I thought--

170
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,399
Come here. Come.

171
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,840
Okay.

172
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,080
Yes, what is it? What?

173
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:31,039
Do you know
that you're extremely handsome?

174
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,280
I know.

175
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,759
- What do you want?
- Can I ask for something?

176
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:38,639
Darling, come on.
I'll do anything for you.

177
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,159
What do you want?

178
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:42,040
I have a craving, dear.

179
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:47,679
What is it? Have I ever not given you
anything you want? No, right?

180
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:49,759
Just tell me what you want. Tell me.

181
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:51,680
I want to ride in a tank.

182
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:53,879
What?

183
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,400
A tank.

184
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,040
A...

185
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:58,520
A tank?

186
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:04,560
That's rather hard to get.

187
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:10,599
Have you heard the viral news
about a woman who has a craving?

188
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:14,319
She wanted to eat soap. Ever heard of it?
That's crazy, right?

189
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,040
Okay, so?

190
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:19,039
You should eat soap because a tank is--

191
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:21,239
You want me to eat soap
so the baby and I die?

192
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:22,719
Metaphor.

193
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:26,120
Dear, I just want to ride in a tank.
I didn't ask for soap.

194
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:27,760
Darling...

195
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,759
Can't you do it?

196
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:34,319
If you can't, sleep outside tonight.

197
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,359
Don't hold the baby or me in your sleep.

198
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,520
- Darling--
- Sleep outside.

199
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:46,639
She planned to sulk for a long time,
but I didn't notice it.

200
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,839
Don't play with me, dear.

201
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,800
I'm a woman of my word.

202
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,159
Where can I find a tank
at a time like this?

203
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:59,640
You're in special forces.
You can't take me for a ride in a tank?

204
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,879
Plus, the baby wants it, not me.

205
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:06,080
Have you ever seen a pilot
bring his plane home?

206
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,800
If you refuse to indulge me, just say so.
No excuses!

207
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:13,960
You sleep outside tonight.
Don't try to sneak in.

208
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,639
Darling.

209
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:21,199
Darling, please open this door.

210
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,280
Okay, listen.
Why don't we go for a ride in my car?

211
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:28,679
I need permission
to take the tank out, darling.

212
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:32,879
No! I didn't ask for much
and it wasn't difficult.

213
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:36,159
It's not difficult for you,
but it is for me.

214
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:39,159
Listen to me. Why don't we...

215
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:40,479
watch YouTube?

216
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,240
No!

217
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,520
Darling, please don't cry.

218
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:51,440
Okay, I'll take you.
I'll go and get it, okay?

219
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,520
Really?

220
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:01,319
- I didn't say anything.
- What did you just say?

221
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:04,680
- I didn't say anything.
- Yes, you said you'd get it.

222
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:07,080
- I said that?
- Yes.

223
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,440
So you'll take it home?

224
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,200
I guess I will.

225
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:13,880
Yes!

226
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,760
Get inside. Stop crying.

227
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,320
I won't.

228
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,200
Dear.

229
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,439
What else do you want?

230
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,720
Please look at me.

231
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,880
I love you.

232
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,200
Yes!

233
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,640
Good job, baby.

234
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:06,320
Darling.

235
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:08,960
Darling.

236
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:17,199
Do you think it's funny?
With your red lipstick and all.

237
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:20,080
You look all, but you're a coward.

238
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:23,560
Anyway, where's the tank?

239
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:27,400
Whose lipstick is that?
Here it is. Ta-dah!

240
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,959
- Did you buy it?
- Of course.

241
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,039
Didn't you say it?

242
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:36,199
If you can't ride on it, that's fine.
As long as you get to look at it.

243
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:40,920
This is the last piece.
Limited edition. The biggest.

244
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,279
- It does look big.
- It is.

245
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,680
How much is it, dear?

246
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,599
Asking about the price?

247
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:49,320
Come on. It's 20,000.

248
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:52,679
How much?

249
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:53,879
20,000.

250
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:55,839
- Dear, you're joking.
- No, I'm not.

251
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:59,399
- What?
- It's so expensive. Such a waste.

252
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,999
Darling, it's more wasteful
if I buy a real tank.

253
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,360
You want to know why?

254
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:08,479
It's hard to park. What if we're going
to KLCC? We can't use the parking space.

255
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:11,479
If we park it by the roadside,
it'll get clamped.

256
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:17,359
If we use the valet, the attendants
won't have a license for a tank.

257
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,399
If we're on the highway,
how do we get through the toll?

258
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:22,439
We can't go to our hometowns.
Darling, it's a waste.

259
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:26,160
We can't be at war
with our children every day.

260
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,000
- Are you asleep?
- Are you done?

261
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,439
No. Want to hear more?

262
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:35,160
Gosh, dear.

263
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:40,400
I hope you like it.

264
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,600
This is 20,000?

265
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:52,640
I didn't say it was in ringgit.
It could be in rupiah.

266
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:04,079
Pregnant women are so rough.

267
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:07,599
- What?
- Huh?

268
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:13,319
Okay. You can go back to sleep, dear.

269
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:15,480
I want to play with this.

270
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:18,960
Darling.

271
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:20,960
Darling, hey!

272
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:24,520
How are you going to play it?
It needs batteries.

273
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,160
Now she's going to the pool. Darling!

274
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:32,160
{\an8}7 MONTHS LATER

275
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:43,760
"What are you cooking?"

276
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,280
Wait.

277
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,520
Chicken chop

278
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:59,840
and carbonara.

279
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:06,839
I will deliver it later.

280
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:08,960
Love, love.

281
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:20,520
<i>Posto! Posto!</i> Bravo! Bravo! Bravo!

282
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,000
"Chicken chop and carbonara."

283
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:43,720
"I will deliver it later."

284
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:47,520
That's cute.

285
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:56,160
You haven't eaten yet,
but you're already full?

286
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:59,120
You little thing.

287
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:23,000
WHY AREN'T YOU EATING?

288
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:26,639
Just say it. It'll be easier.

289
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,600
Don't you miss my voice?

290
00:19:33,080 --> 00:19:34,519
I can speak?

291
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:36,719
You're just trying to make me angry.

292
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:38,079
You wanted the silent treatment.

293
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:40,639
I thought I could only speak
in seven or eight months.

294
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:44,159
Apparently, it's just a week.
No thrill at all.

295
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:46,439
You want it? After the baby is born?

296
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:48,079
No, no. I was just kidding.

297
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:49,640
There you go.

298
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:53,520
Luckily, I'm missing you, dear.

299
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,439
Otherwise, you'd have
to sleep outside, by the pool.

300
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:59,160
I can't swim. What if I fall in?

301
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:03,319
- Special forces, but can't swim?
- No, I do.

302
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:05,079
- I forgot about it.
- You forgot?

303
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,520
I want to sleep upstairs.

304
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:13,200
Darling.

305
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:18,120
- Dear.
- Yes.

306
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,840
I am so happy right now.

307
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:27,400
I've never felt this happy before
in my life.

308
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:32,839
Can we stay like this forever and ever?

309
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:36,479
Yes. Yes, we can. I want that too.

310
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:38,399
We'll live like this forever.

311
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:40,560
- Forever?
- Forever.

312
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:46,959
I'll check.
I'll come back and accompany you.

313
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,960
Make it quick.

314
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:16,159
We received reports of pirate activity
on land that's threatening public safety.

315
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,959
Two of our men were sent to Sabah.

316
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:19,919
Simple mission. Go wander.

317
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:22,879
Gather intel on their activities
and report back.

318
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:25,240
They should have been back three days ago,

319
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,160
but we haven't heard from them.

320
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:32,159
<i>We lost all contact</i>

321
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:34,160
<i>and the villagers said that they're...</i>

322
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:36,720
missing.

323
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:40,079
Captured by the pirates?

324
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:45,320
Yes, but we don't know
whether they're still alive.

325
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,360
But you know it, right?

326
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:50,840
I'm on leave now.

327
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:53,360
Radwa could give birth at any time now.

328
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:56,040
Yes, Ridz. I know.

329
00:21:56,760 --> 00:22:00,599
The intel said that those pirates
are on the Sabah border,

330
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:02,040
near an Indonesian village.

331
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,279
<i>Their temporary camp, Ridz.</i>

332
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:13,039
Mr. Omar wants you
to lead this rescue mission.

333
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,840
Bring those two men back.

334
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,320
Dead or alive.

335
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:21,919
There are other soldiers.

336
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:25,239
Ridz, this is
not a regular rescue mission.

337
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:27,199
Mr. Omar wants the best to lead.

338
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,839
And you, Ridz, are our best.

339
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:32,519
I won't go on a mission
till Radwa finishes her confinement.

340
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:35,280
- That's my deal with Mr. Man.
- He's on sick leave.

341
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:38,200
Mr. Omar has taken over everything.

342
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:42,200
This is a non-negotiable order, Ridz.

343
00:22:43,160 --> 00:22:45,600
Bring our men back.

344
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:51,319
In case Mr. Omar doesn't know,
Adrean is there.

345
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,440
He should've told Mr. Omar about this.

346
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:02,840
Megat.

347
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,480
Who are

348
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:07,840
those two missing men?

349
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,400
Adrean.

350
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:26,760
Oh God!

351
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,160
Who's the other one?

352
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:41,840
Haider.

353
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:04,720
- It's okay, dear.
- It's not okay.

354
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:09,360
- They need you.
- You need me too, darling.

355
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:13,760
I have to be with you. I promised you.

356
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,960
They are your brothers.

357
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,360
But you are my everything.

358
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:28,120
I don't want to go.

359
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:32,360
You have to go, dear.

360
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:38,760
I love you so much.

361
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,440
I love you more.

362
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,720
Ridz, please bring him back.

363
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,640
Please save him.

364
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:11,080
Dear.

365
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:17,080
I know this is not the right time
to say this.

366
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,880
There will never be the right time.

367
00:25:25,040 --> 00:25:26,600
But if

368
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:30,840
this is the last time I'm seeing you,

369
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:36,200
I want you to know that you are
the best gift God has given me.

370
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:46,400
I really love you.
More than my own life, dear.

371
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:51,920
I know I made a lot of mistakes with you.

372
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,320
I've troubled you.

373
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:57,800
Please forgive me, dear.

374
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:06,360
Please consider me free
of any debt to you.

375
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,480
I forgive you.

376
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:13,160
You're free of any debt to me.

377
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:21,400
Forgive me for all of my mistakes.

378
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:26,560
You've never made
any mistakes with me, dear.

379
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:48,360
I'll always be with you, darling.

380
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:57,920
My baby.

381
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,600
Wait for me to come home.

382
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,680
I want to accompany your mom

383
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:12,520
when you come out.

384
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:23,120
Darling,

385
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:26,600
I'll see you when I see you.

386
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:35,640
Boys, let's go.

387
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:16,240
- Two barns. One cadet, another's clear.
- Got it.

388
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:32,680
Megat, cover me!

389
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:35,680
Okay.

390
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:55,119
I thought it was just Braxton Hicks.
So I held it in.

391
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:58,559
The opening of your cervix is 7 cm.
Get ready for delivery.

392
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:00,839
Nurse, take her to the labor room.

393
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:04,439
Doctor, can you wait?
I want to wait for my husband.

394
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,720
Ma'am, it's 7 cm. Get ready for delivery.

395
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:09,640
I want my husband!

396
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:40,759
In the name of God.

397
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:42,280
Okay. Push, ma'am!

398
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:47,320
Bastards.

399
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,999
Hey. Hey, Adrean.

400
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,040
Adrean, I'm here.

401
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:12,720
I'm here. I'm right here with you.

402
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:16,240
I'm here.

403
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:43,680
Let's go. Hurry. Faster.

404
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:48,120
Adrean, come on. Megat, cover!

405
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:55,920
It hurts. I can't.

406
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:35,560
Take Adrean.

407
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:43,640
Get them out of here. Don't stop. Go.

408
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,680
Now!

409
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:04,160
Daniel, cover them.

410
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:06,080
And you?

411
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:07,639
I'll cover here.

412
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:10,440
I'll make sure the enemies are delayed.
Go and rescue them.

413
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:13,640
You go. I'll cover here.

414
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:15,680
Daniel, go.

415
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:24,759
Radwa's waiting for you.
Why are you still here?

416
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:27,920
- This is an order!
- You're still my brother, Thariq!

417
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,680
My brother!

418
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:34,960
It hurts.

419
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:40,639
Dear. It hurts, dear.

420
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:43,160
You saved me from Zahid before.

421
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:46,080
I owe my life to you.

422
00:32:47,800 --> 00:32:49,040
Now it's my turn.

423
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:52,320
Radwa is waiting for you.

424
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:55,280
Now, go.

425
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,280
Go!

426
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:08,800
Promise me you'll be safe.

427
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,280
I'll be fine.

428
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,080
Now go.

429
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:29,280
T.

430
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:34,200
H.

431
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,120
A.

432
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:42,760
R.

433
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:45,640
I place my trust in God.

434
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,240
Time to go to work.

435
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:58,800
I.

436
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:21,920
My child hasn't met
the crazy Uncle Daniel.

437
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:25,040
Let's go.

438
00:34:31,520 --> 00:34:32,560
Q.

439
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,639
Darling.

440
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:45,080
I promised I'd be with you.

441
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:51,840
I can't wait to see our child.

442
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:09,240
Push more, ma'am. A bit more.

443
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:31,960
Just a bit more, ma'am.

444
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:56,640
Congratulations, ma'am. It's a girl.

445
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:21,320
Dear.

446
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:25,560
Our baby has been born, dear.

447
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,320
Hurry home.

448
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:41,000
Thariq. Get up, Thariq.

449
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:43,959
You're going to be a dad.

450
00:36:43,960 --> 00:36:45,240
Oh, God!

451
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,599
God, help me.

452
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:50,200
Thariq, wake up, please. Thariq!

453
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:53,480
Thariq!

454
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:57,680
Thariq, please wake up. Ridz, come on.

455
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:02,800
You have your dad's eyes.

456
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:04,760
So pretty.

457
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,080
If I'm not here,

458
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:17,080
please take care of your dad for me.

459
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:28,480
Madam, the doctor asked me
to inject some medicine for you.

460
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,240
Take the baby.

461
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:43,560
Bye, Tia.

462
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:46,240
What did you say?

463
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,280
Tia Radia.

464
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:51,040
The daughter of Thariq Ridzuwan.

465
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:54,480
Such a pretty name.

466
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:48,560
- Mom.
- Sweetie.

467
00:38:56,160 --> 00:38:58,360
Darling. Haider.

468
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,080
Are you okay?

469
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:05,240
I'm okay, darling.

470
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:07,600
I'm at the hospital now.

471
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:11,000
Thank God.

472
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:14,000
Darling, where's Ridz?

473
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:17,519
<i>Radwa is giving birth now. She needs Ridz.</i>

474
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:19,879
He has to come now.

475
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:22,519
He has to come and accompany Radwa.

476
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,920
Ma'am.

477
00:39:25,080 --> 00:39:26,639
I'm so sorry.

478
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:29,240
Mrs. Radwa couldn't be saved.

479
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:41,960
Thalia.

480
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:44,840
Lia...

481
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:53,400
Darling.

482
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:59,120
Radwa is gone. She's gone.

483
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:51,879
The bullet went straight through.

484
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:54,320
Order a CT scan as soon as possible.

485
00:40:58,840 --> 00:41:00,239
Radwa.

486
00:41:00,240 --> 00:41:01,440
Doctor.

487
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:04,879
Can we transfer this patient
to a hospital in KL?

488
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:06,600
His wife is due any time now.

489
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:09,800
- Let me check on him first.
- No. Make it happen.

490
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:11,360
Thank you.

491
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:17,560
How are you? Okay?

492
00:41:18,520 --> 00:41:20,480
Radwa has given birth.

493
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:25,320
Thank God. I'll tell Ridz.

494
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:33,720
Radwa is gone.

495
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:04,080
Hang on, Ridz. Hey, come on.
Just a bit more.

496
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:26,480
Radwa?

497
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:36,840
Where's Radwa?

498
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:42,600
Radwa has given birth, Ridz.

499
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:44,680
It's a baby girl.

500
00:42:46,080 --> 00:42:47,800
Thank God.

501
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:01,800
I want to see Radwa.

502
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:05,080
There was

503
00:43:06,320 --> 00:43:10,280
a complication during birth.

504
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:14,240
Radwa...

505
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:22,519
Radwa's gone, Ridz.

506
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:25,479
Let me see Radwa, Dad.

507
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:27,760
- Don't joke around.
- Ridz.

508
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,640
Radwa is gone.

509
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:37,920
From God we came, to God we shall return.

510
00:43:43,280 --> 00:43:46,280
Don't joke around, Dad.

511
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:55,840
Please don't joke around like this.

512
00:43:57,920 --> 00:43:59,640
No, Radwa is here.

513
00:44:02,560 --> 00:44:03,800
No.

514
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:09,200
No!

515
00:44:40,920 --> 00:44:42,160
Get out.

516
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:44,840
Get out!

517
00:45:35,560 --> 00:45:37,040
- Darling.
- Ridz.

518
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:42,320
Darling.

519
00:45:44,200 --> 00:45:46,000
Please don't leave me.

520
00:45:47,360 --> 00:45:49,240
Why did you leave me?

521
00:45:51,600 --> 00:45:54,280
- Ridz.
- Darling.

522
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:04,360
Wake up, please. Wake up.

523
00:46:10,040 --> 00:46:10,880
Ridz.

524
00:46:24,360 --> 00:46:27,759
Ridz!

525
00:46:27,760 --> 00:46:29,080
Help!

526
00:46:29,640 --> 00:46:30,519
{\an8}Thariq.

527
00:46:30,520 --> 00:46:34,320
{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED

528
00:46:39,920 --> 00:46:41,559
{\an8}I've always wanted her to die.

529
00:46:41,560 --> 00:46:45,239
{\an8}God has granted my prayers.

530
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:46,479
{\an8}She's dead now.

531
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:49,839
{\an8}You promised to be with me
when I deliver the baby,

532
00:46:49,840 --> 00:46:51,440
{\an8}but you never came.

533
00:46:52,160 --> 00:46:54,600
{\an8}You were not there when I died.

534
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:56,519
{\an8}Let's take her child.

535
00:46:56,520 --> 00:46:58,919
{\an8}Hey! Over my dead body.

536
00:46:58,920 --> 00:47:01,159
{\an8}I don't want her descendants
to live in my house.

537
00:47:01,160 --> 00:47:03,599
{\an8}Let me stay here! Why not?

538
00:47:03,600 --> 00:47:05,959
{\an8}There's no problem here.
No mission, no work.

539
00:47:05,960 --> 00:47:07,879
{\an8}No Farez, no Aina. Nothing!

540
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,280
{\an8}Just the two of us.

